<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Male. Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6A, C</figureCitation>
). Black, covered with white pollinosity, ocellar triangle, and a large triangular macula on the front, brown pilose, pile on front black, on gena and face white pilose, on ocellar triangle black pilose, on the occiput white except for the dorsal pile, which are black, frontal triangle golden metallic. Antennae brown, orange-red ventrally, oval, longer than wide pedicel and the lower basal corner of basoflagellomere, ratio 1.0:1.1:2.9, arista orange, dark brown toward the tip. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Thorax</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6C</figureCitation>
). Black, scutum shining, with iridescent to opaque reflections, with two median brownish pollinose vittae on anterior half. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Wing</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6C</figureCitation>
). Slightly smoky, the stigma brownish, membrane microtrichose, except for extensive bare areas on basal half (cells, sc, r1, dm and bm); costal cell hyaline, bare on basal 1/2; marginal maculae restricted to surrounding areas of veins R1, R4+5 and M1 apically; tegula black pilose, basicosta yellow pilose, alula bare medially, calypter whitish, border whitish, fringe yellow, plumula yellow, halter yellow, knob white. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Legs</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6C</figureCitation>
). Yellow, pro- and mesofemur yellow; metafemur brown, except orange on basal 1/5 and apical 1/5; pro and mesotibia orange, metatibia extensively brown, only orange brownish on basal 2/3; probasitarsomere, meso- and metabasitarsomere I-II yellow, the pile yellow, black on the metatibia and above on the tarsi. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6B</figureCitation>
). Elongate, black, the first tergum shining black, orange laterally, the second tergum with a broad macula reaching apical 1/3 laterally; third tergum with a broad triangular macula, which is short in the fourth tergum; fourth and fifth sterna black pilose. Pile orange on the sides basally, as well as in the maculae, black down the middle and on the terga apex. Male genitalia as Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male genitalia: A whole genitalia including epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view B epandrium, dorsal view C hypandrium, ventral view. Scale bar: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402761" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">7</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Female.</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6D-F</figureCitation>
). Similar to male except for normal sexual dimorphism. Frons with pollinose transversal maculae below. Abdominal maculae are comparatively shorter than in the male and indistinguishable in the fourth tergum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Length</emphasis>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">N</emphasis>
= 4). Body 12.4-12.6 mm; wing 11.3-11.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="puntarena" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="puntarena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">puntarena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a noun in apposition and refers to the province where the type series was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montoya" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Argentinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argentinomyia puntarena" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puntarena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Argentinomyia puntarena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">N</emphasis>
= 5) is distributed through the west slope of the 
<taxonomicName genus="Talamanca" lsidName="Talamanca" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="genus">Talamanca</taxonomicName>
Cordillera in Costa Rica (Puntarenas, San 
<normalizedToken originalValue="José">Jose</normalizedToken>
) at an elevation between 1000 to 2550 m. a.s.l., in the province of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Puntarena-Chiriquí">Puntarena-Chiriqui</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Biogeographical distribution of Argentinomyia huitepecensis sp. nov. (green), A. talamanca sp. nov. (red) and A. puntarenas sp. nov. (blue)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402770" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">16</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montoya" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Argentinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argentinomyia puntarena" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puntarena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Argentinomyia puntarena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. occurs in sympatry with 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. talamanca" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="talamanca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">A. talamanca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. in the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Puntarena-Chiriquí">Puntarena-Chiriqui</normalizedToken>
province.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
